{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "DahnekeCondensationEvaporation",
        "description": "Coupled mass and heat transfer for stationary droplet condensation or evaporation with Dahneke transition-regime corrections. Combines DahnekeMassTransportCorrection (Eq. 5.5) and DahnekeHeatTransportCorrection (Eq. 5.7) with Maxwell flux equations (Eqs. 2.1–2.2) to give transition-regime corrected molecular growth rate I and heat conduction rate Q. Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl `DahnekeCondensationEvaporation`.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "condensation",
            "evaporation",
            "mass-transfer",
            "heat-transfer",
            "transition-regime",
            "dahneke",
            "knudsen-number"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "Aerosol.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-ivb)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Dahneke, B. (1983). Simple Kinetic Theory of Brownian Diffusion in Vapors and Aerosols. In Theory of Dispersed Multiphase Flow (pp. 97–133). Academic Press. Eqs. 2.1–2.3, 5.4–5.8 (condensation/evaporation with transition-regime mass and heat transport corrections)."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "DahnekeCondensationEvaporation": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Dahneke, B. (1983) Simple Kinetic Theory of Brownian Diffusion in Vapors and Aerosols. Theory of Dispersed Multiphase Flow, Academic Press, Eqs. 2.1–2.3, 5.4–5.8 — coupled mass and heat transport to a sphere with Dahneke transition-regime corrections. Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl `DahnekeCondensationEvaporation` (esm-ivb).",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@481d5b6:src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl:157\n\nUpstream `DahnekeCondensationEvaporation` is an MTK `@component` that composes two subsystems:\n  mass_corr = DahnekeMassTransportCorrection (Eq. 5.5) — 4 algebraic equations\n  heat_corr = DahnekeHeatTransportCorrection (Eq. 5.7) — 2 algebraic equations\nPlus 4 top-level equations (Eqs. 2.1, 5.4, 2.2, 5.6) for the corrected fluxes.\n\nSubsystem variable mapping into flat ESM namespace:\n  mass_corr.c_bar  → c_bar_v  (mean thermal velocity of vapor, Eq. 6.2)\n  mass_corr.ℓ_D   → ell_D    (diffusional mean-free-path of vapor, Eq. 3.6)\n  mass_corr.Kn_D  → Kn_D     (diffusion Knudsen number, ℓ_D/r)\n  mass_corr.β     → β_m      (mass transport correction factor, Eq. 5.5)\n  heat_corr.Kn_K  → Kn_K     (heat transfer Knudsen number, Eq. 5.7)\n  heat_corr.β_q   → β_q      (heat transport correction factor, Eq. 5.7)\n\nParameters from mass_corr:\n  k_B = 1.380649e-23 J/K (Boltzmann constant, @constants in Julia, folded as literal)\n  m_v = 4.81e-26 kg (mass of vapor molecule; default is N2, replace with species mass)\n  δ_m = 1.0 (condensation-evaporation sticking coefficient, dimensionless)\n\nParameters from heat_corr:\n  n_gas     = 2.46e25 m⁻³  (number concentration of gas, STP air)\n  c_bar_gas = 500.0 m/s    (mean thermal velocity of gas molecules, air at 298 K)\n  c_v       = 718.0 J/(kg·K) (specific heat at constant volume, air)\n  m_gas     = 4.81e-26 kg  (mass of gas molecule, N2)\n  α_t       = 1.0          (thermal accommodation coefficient, dimensionless)\n\nShared parameters (connected via param_to_var in Julia):\n  r = 1.0e-7 m      (droplet radius, shared by both subsystems)\n  D_v = 2.0e-5 m²/s (vapor diffusion coefficient, shared with mass_corr)\n  κ = 0.026 W/(m·K) (thermal conductivity, shared with heat_corr)\n\nTop-level parameters:\n  T_inf = 298.15 K, T_o = 293.15 K  (gas and surface temperatures)\n  n_inf = 1.0e21 m⁻³, n_s = 0.0 m⁻³ (vapor concentrations)\n  L_vap = 7.48e-20 J  (molecular latent heat; present in source but not used in any\n    equation — retained for external energy-balance use, e.g. Eq. 5.8 β·I_M = β_q·Q_M/L)\n\nEquation chain:\n  c_bar_v = sqrt(8 k_B T_inf / (π m_v))               [Eq. 6.2, vapor thermal speed]\n  ell_D   = 2 D_v / c_bar_v                            [Eq. 3.6, diffusional MFP]\n  Kn_D    = ell_D / r                                   [diffusion Knudsen number]\n  β_m     = (Kn_D+1) / (2 Kn_D(Kn_D+1)/δ_m + 1)     [Eq. 5.5, mass correction]\n  Kn_K    = 2κ / (c_bar_gas n_gas m_gas c_v r)         [Eq. 5.7, heat Knudsen number]\n  β_q     = (Kn_K+1) / (2 Kn_K(Kn_K+1)/α_t + 1)     [Eq. 5.7, heat correction]\n  I_M     = 4π r D_v (n_inf − n_s)                     [Eq. 2.1, Maxwell growth rate]\n  I       = β_m · I_M                                   [Eq. 5.4, corrected growth rate]\n  Q_M     = 4π r κ (T_inf − T_o)                       [Eq. 2.2, Maxwell heat rate]\n  Q       = β_q · Q_M                                   [Eq. 5.6, corrected heat rate]\n\nDefault conditions (r=100 nm, T_inf=298.15 K):\n  Kn_D ≈ 0.857 (transition regime for mass), β_m ≈ 0.444\n  Kn_K ≈ 1.224 (transition regime for heat), β_q ≈ 0.345\n  I_M ≈ 2.513e10 s⁻¹, I ≈ 1.116e10 s⁻¹\n  Q_M ≈ 1.634e-7 W,  Q ≈ 5.637e-8 W\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-12): all variables are purely algebraic (observed). The expression chain has depth ≤ 5 (T_inf → c_bar_v → ell_D → Kn_D → β_m → I). Float64 round-off accumulates to ~5×1e-16 per node ≈ 2e-15 total. rel=1e-12 leaves three orders of headroom."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-12
            },
            "variables": {
                "m_v": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg",
                    "default": 4.81e-26,
                    "description": "Mass of a single vapor molecule. Default 4.81e-26 kg ≈ mass of N₂ (0.028 kg/mol / Avogadro). Replace with the actual species molecular mass for the condensing vapor (e.g. 2.99e-26 kg for H₂O, 1.64e-25 kg for H₂SO₄)."
                },
                "T_inf": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 298.15,
                    "description": "Gas temperature at infinity (far-field). Used to compute the mean thermal velocity of vapor molecules c_bar_v and hence the diffusion Knudsen number. Default 298.15 K (25°C, standard atmospheric conditions)."
                },
                "T_o": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 293.15,
                    "description": "Droplet surface temperature. The Maxwell heat conduction rate Q_M is proportional to (T_inf − T_o). Default 293.15 K (20°C), giving a 5 K subcooling relative to the default T_inf. Set T_o > T_inf for net outward heat flux."
                },
                "D_v": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "default": 2e-05,
                    "description": "Diffusion coefficient of vapor molecules in the carrier gas. Default 2×10⁻⁵ m²/s is representative of atmospheric trace gases in air at 298 K and 1 atm. Used in both ell_D (via c_bar_v) and the Maxwell flux I_M."
                },
                "r": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1e-07,
                    "description": "Droplet (particle) radius. Shared input to both mass and heat transport subsystems. Default 100 nm places the system in the transition regime (Kn_D ≈ 0.86, Kn_K ≈ 1.22 at default conditions)."
                },
                "δ_m": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Condensation-evaporation (sticking) coefficient: probability that a vapor molecule hitting the surface is absorbed. Dimensionless, range (0, 1]. Default 1.0 (perfect sticking). Controls the free-molecular limit of β_m: β_m → δ_m/(2 Kn_D) as Kn_D → ∞."
                },
                "κ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/(m*K)",
                    "default": 0.026,
                    "description": "Thermal conductivity of the carrier gas. Shared input to both Kn_K and Q_M. Default 0.026 W/(m·K) is air at 298 K. Used in both the heat Knudsen number and the Maxwell heat flux Q_M = 4π r κ (T_inf − T_o)."
                },
                "n_gas": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 2.46e+25,
                    "description": "Number concentration of gas molecules. Used in the heat Knudsen number Kn_K via the volumetric heat capacity n_gas × m_gas × c_v. Default 2.46×10²⁵ m⁻³ is air at STP (Loschmidt constant)."
                },
                "c_bar_gas": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 500.0,
                    "description": "Mean thermal velocity of gas (carrier) molecules. Used in the heat Knudsen number Kn_K = 2κ/(c_bar_gas n_gas m_gas c_v r). Default 500 m/s is approximate for N₂ at 298 K (exact value: ~476 m/s; 500 m/s is a round number used in the source)."
                },
                "c_v": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/(kg*K)",
                    "default": 718.0,
                    "description": "Specific heat at constant volume of the carrier gas (per unit mass). Used in Kn_K via the volumetric heat capacity. Default 718.0 J/(kg·K) is for air (diatomic ideal gas: c_v = (5/2)(R/M_air) ≈ 718 J/(kg·K))."
                },
                "m_gas": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg",
                    "default": 4.81e-26,
                    "description": "Mass of a single gas (carrier) molecule. Used in Kn_K to form the volumetric heat capacity n_gas × m_gas × c_v. Default 4.81e-26 kg ≈ N₂ (0.028 kg/mol / Avogadro). Should match the actual carrier gas species."
                },
                "α_t": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Thermal accommodation coefficient: fraction of impinging gas molecules that fully thermally accommodate to the droplet surface. Dimensionless, range (0, 1]. Default 1.0 (perfect thermal accommodation). Controls the free-molecular limit of β_q: β_q → α_t/(2 Kn_K) as Kn_K → ∞."
                },
                "n_inf": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1e+21,
                    "description": "Vapor number concentration at infinity (far-field). The Maxwell flux I_M is proportional to (n_inf − n_s). When n_inf > n_s, condensation occurs (I > 0); when n_inf < n_s, evaporation occurs (I < 0). Default 1×10²¹ m⁻³."
                },
                "n_s": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Saturation vapor number concentration at the droplet surface. When n_s = 0 the droplet is a perfect absorber (all vapor condenses). Set n_s > 0 for an evaporating or partially saturated droplet. Default 0.0."
                },
                "L_vap": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J",
                    "default": 7.48e-20,
                    "description": "Molecular latent heat of vaporization. Provided in the source component but not directly used in the algebraic equations here. Retained for external use in the Dahneke energy balance (Eq. 5.8): β·I_M = β_q·Q_M/L_vap, which couples mass and heat transport at steady state. Default 7.48e-20 J ≈ latent heat of water (44.0 kJ/mol / Avogadro)."
                },
                "c_bar_v": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Mean thermal velocity of vapor molecules, Eq. 6.2: c_bar_v = sqrt(8 k_B T_inf / (π m_v)). The diffusional mean-free-path ell_D = 2 D_v / c_bar_v (Eq. 3.6) depends on c_bar_v. Increases with T_inf^(1/2) and decreases with m_v^(1/2). At default conditions ≈ 466.8 m/s.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "sqrt",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            8.0,
                                            1.380649e-23,
                                            "T_inf"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            3.141592653589793,
                                            "m_v"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "ell_D": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Diffusional mean-free-path of vapor molecules, Eq. 3.6: ell_D = 2 D_v / c_bar_v. This length scale governs the onset of non-continuum effects in mass transport. When ell_D ≪ r (Kn_D ≪ 1) the continuum diffusion equations hold; when ell_D ≫ r (Kn_D ≫ 1) free-molecular kinetics dominate. At default conditions ≈ 85.7 nm.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    2.0,
                                    "D_v"
                                ]
                            },
                            "c_bar_v"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "Kn_D": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Diffusion Knudsen number for mass transport: Kn_D = ell_D / r. Kn_D ≪ 1 = continuum regime (β_m → 1); Kn_D ≫ 1 = free-molecular regime (β_m → δ_m/(2 Kn_D)). At default conditions Kn_D ≈ 0.857, placing the system in the transition regime.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            "ell_D",
                            "r"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "β_m": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Mass transport correction factor, Eq. 5.5: β_m = (Kn_D+1) / (2 Kn_D(Kn_D+1)/δ_m + 1). Reduces the Maxwell molecular flux I_M to the actual transition-regime flux I = β_m·I_M. Limits: β_m → 1 as Kn_D → 0; β_m → δ_m/(2 Kn_D) → 0 as Kn_D → ∞. At default conditions β_m ≈ 0.444.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    "Kn_D",
                                    1.0
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    2.0,
                                                    "Kn_D",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "+",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "Kn_D",
                                                            1.0
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "δ_m"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    1.0
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "Kn_K": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Heat transfer Knudsen number, Eq. 5.7: Kn_K = 2κ / (c_bar_gas n_gas m_gas c_v r). The denominator c_bar_gas·n_gas·m_gas·c_v·r is proportional to the continuum heat flux per unit temperature difference. Kn_K ≪ 1 = continuum heat transfer (β_q → 1); Kn_K ≫ 1 = free-molecular heat transfer. At default conditions Kn_K ≈ 1.224.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    2.0,
                                    "κ"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "c_bar_gas",
                                    "n_gas",
                                    "m_gas",
                                    "c_v",
                                    "r"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "β_q": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Heat transport correction factor, Eq. 5.7: β_q = (Kn_K+1) / (2 Kn_K(Kn_K+1)/α_t + 1). Reduces the Maxwell heat conduction rate Q_M to the actual transition-regime rate Q = β_q·Q_M. Limits: β_q → 1 as Kn_K → 0; β_q → α_t/(2 Kn_K) → 0 as Kn_K → ∞. At default conditions β_q ≈ 0.345.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    "Kn_K",
                                    1.0
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    2.0,
                                                    "Kn_K",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "+",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "Kn_K",
                                                            1.0
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "α_t"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    1.0
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "I_M": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "description": "Maxwell (continuum) molecular growth rate, Eq. 2.1: I_M = 4π r D_v (n_inf − n_s). This is the continuum-regime diffusion-limited flux. Positive = condensation, negative = evaporation. The actual rate I = β_m·I_M is reduced by the transition-regime correction β_m ≤ 1. At default conditions I_M ≈ 2.513×10¹⁰ s⁻¹.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            4.0,
                            3.141592653589793,
                            "r",
                            "D_v",
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [
                                    "n_inf",
                                    "n_s"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "I": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "description": "Corrected molecular growth rate, Eq. 5.4: I = β_m · I_M. The transition-regime mass flux to the droplet in molecules per second. Multiply by the molecular mass m_v to get the mass flux dm/dt = m_v·I. The droplet radius growth rate is dr/dt = m_v·I / (4π r² ρ_liquid). At default conditions I ≈ 1.116×10¹⁰ s⁻¹.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "β_m",
                            "I_M"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "Q_M": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "W",
                    "description": "Maxwell (continuum) heat conduction rate, Eq. 2.2: Q_M = 4π r κ (T_inf − T_o). Positive = heat flows from gas to droplet (droplet is cooler). The actual rate Q = β_q·Q_M is reduced by the transition-regime correction β_q ≤ 1. At default conditions (ΔT = 5 K) Q_M ≈ 1.634×10⁻⁷ W.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            4.0,
                            3.141592653589793,
                            "r",
                            "κ",
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [
                                    "T_inf",
                                    "T_o"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "Q": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "W",
                    "description": "Corrected heat conduction rate, Eq. 5.6: Q = β_q · Q_M. The transition-regime heat flux to the droplet in watts. At steady state, latent heat release from condensation balances heat conduction: L_vap·I = Q, giving the Dahneke energy balance (Eq. 5.8) β_m·I_M = β_q·Q_M/L_vap. At default conditions Q ≈ 5.637×10⁻⁸ W.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "β_q",
                            "Q_M"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            },
            "equations": [],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_conditions",
                    "description": "Default parameters: r=100 nm, T_inf=298.15 K, T_o=293.15 K, D_v=2×10⁻⁵ m²/s, n_inf=10²¹ m⁻³, n_s=0. Both mass (Kn_D≈0.857) and heat (Kn_K≈1.224) are in the transition regime. Expected: β_m≈0.444, β_q≈0.345, I≈1.116×10¹⁰ s⁻¹, Q≈5.637×10⁻⁸ W.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
