                {
                    "id": "continuum_limit_large_r",
                    "description": "Continuum limit: r=0.01 m (macroscopic droplet). Both Kn_D≈8.6×10⁻⁶ and Kn_K≈1.2×10⁻⁵ are ≪ 1, so β_m → 1 and β_q → 1. The corrected fluxes approach the Maxwell continuum values: I ≈ I_M, Q ≈ Q_M. Verifies that the transition-regime corrections vanish as r → ∞.",
